  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel and finely chop the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Top, tail, and finely dice the<strong> carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/big-flavour-lean-beef-lasagne/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped onion </strong>and<strong> diced carrot</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 4 min or until softened</p><p>Boil half a kettle, then peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/big-flavour-lean-beef-lasagne/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion and carrot have softened, add the <strong>lean beef mince</strong> to the pan and increase the heat to high</p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until browned all over, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/big-flavour-lean-beef-lasagne/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve the <strong>beef stock mix</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>Henderson's Relish</strong>, <strong>dried oregano </strong>and a pinch of<strong> sugar</strong> in 250ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [450ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your<strong> tomato stock</strong></p><p>Grate the<strong> cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/big-flavour-lean-beef-lasagne/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the beef has browned, tear the <strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong> into the pan with your hands</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add the<strong> tomato stock</strong> with a generous grind of<strong> black pepper </strong>and cook for 5-7 min or until thickened to a ragù-like consistency – this is your<strong> ragù</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/big-flavour-lean-beef-lasagne/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, melt 20g <span class=\"text-danger\">[40g]</span> <strong>butter</strong> in a pot over a medium heat</p><p>Once melted, add 20g <span class=\"text-danger\">[40g]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1 min or until a sandy paste forms – this is your <strong>roux</strong></p><p>Add 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml] </span><strong>milk </strong>gradually and whisk for 5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains</p><p>Remove from the heat, season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and stir through <strong>half</strong> the <strong>grated</strong> <strong>cheese </strong>– this is your<strong> béchamel</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/big-flavour-lean-beef-lasagne/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Layer some of the <strong>ragù</strong> over the bottom of an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong>, then top with 3 <strong>lasagne sheets</strong>, being careful not to overlap the pasta</p><p>Repeat this process until you end up with a final layer of lasagne sheets (you may need to layer differently depending on the size of your dish)</p><p>Cover with the <strong>béchamel</strong>, top with the<strong> remaining grated cheese</strong> and cook in the oven for 30 min or until the pasta is cooked</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/big-flavour-lean-beef-lasagne/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>balsamic vinegar </strong>with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your<strong> dressing</strong></p><p>Wash the <strong>mixed leaf salad</strong>, then pat it dry with <strong>kitchen paper</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>lean beef</strong> <strong>lasagne</strong> with the<strong> mixed leaf salad </strong>to the side and the <strong>dressing </strong>drizzled over and enjoy!</p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Loved this recipe? Us too! That's why it's one of our Everyday Favourites, available every week.</span></strong></p>",
      "order": 8
    }
